HEADWORD: Supping
<hw>Sup"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of one who sups; the act of taking supper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is supped; broth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supplace</ent>⟦br⟧
